ce:section.ce:para:
Although the MEF effect has previously been explained based on the interaction between the electric field created by a metal and the electron oscillations on a metal surface induced by an excited fluorophore, whether the metal or fluorophore emits the light is still subject to debate [7,33,34]. To understand our experimental results, single nanoparticle scattering spectra of each PEGylated AuNC and AuNC-CND complex (Fig. 5
                        A–B


                        ) and their dark-field microscope images (Fig. 5C–D) were obtained. The average scattering intensity was calculated from 88 to 100 individual AuNC-CND particles for each sample. Scattering analysis of the ∼17 nm AuNCs could not be conducted due to the weak signal intensity caused by their small size (<30 nm).
